      "paper_id": "PMC12783088",
      "text_span_id": "discussion_2",
      "text": "Dysregulated Wnt/\u03b2-catenin signaling is implicated in ~40% of HCC cases. This pathway's aberrant activation, often due to mutations in components like CTNNB1 (encoding \u03b2-catenin), plays a significant role in HCC pathogenesis.",
