  "notes": [
    "This study represents a comparative genomic analysis of hepatocellular carcinoma between chimpanzees and humans, revealing species-specific mutational patterns and oncogenic pathways.",
    "The high frequency of TSC2 mutations in chimpanzee HCC (80%) compared to human HCC (~7%) suggests divergent evolutionary pathways in cancer development.",
    "The study utilized both whole genome and whole exome sequencing approaches to characterize somatic mutations in chimpanzee HCC samples."
  ]
